## II. HTML ID Rules

IDs must be unique and are primarily used for targeting elements with JavaScript, fragment links, or accessibility.

| Rule ID | Constraint | Naming Convention | Primary Use Cases |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :--- |
| **R7** | **Uniqueness** | N/A | An ID must be unique across the entire HTML page. |
| **R8** | **Case Style** | `camelCase` or `kebab-case` | Be consistent with the project's chosen style (often `camelCase` to align with JavaScript variables). |
| **R9** | **Form Association** | ID on input matches `for` on label | Used to link a `<label>` to its form input (e.g., `<label for="email">` pairs with `<input id="email">`). |

