## III. ARIA Naming Rules (Accessibility)

ARIA attributes are crucial for providing semantic information to assistive technologies.

| Rule ID | Attribute | Priority/Precedence | Use Case and Order of Operation |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :--- |
| **R10** | **`aria-labelledby`** | **Highest** | **PREFFERED.** Reference a visible element's ID to use its content as the accessible name. It overrides other naming methods. |
| **R11** | **`aria-label`** | Second | Provide a direct, non-visible text string as the accessible name. Use only when visible text cannot be referenced (e.g., an icon-only button). |
| **R12** | **`aria-describedby`** | N/A | Reference an element containing a longer description, instructions, or contextual help (separate from the main accessible name). |
| **R13** | **Native First** | N/A | Use semantic HTML elements (e.g., `<button>`) before applying ARIA roles (e.g., `role="button"`). |

